Episode 416 is the sixteenth episode of the fourth season of Square One TV, and the one-hundred seventy-first episode overall.

Starring:

Guest Starring: Joe Palmieri (O. Dean Middlemun), Bernive Massi (Hestor Phestor), Herscel Sparber (Marion "Mad Dog" Fist)

Segments

Square One Challenge: Randy vs. Sharon

2 students try to determine whether each of 2 cast members is blyffing or telling the truth when aswering the questions: Boxes with Triangles, T-Shirts and Shorts, Dodecahedron Die

Dick & Vern: Cartablanca Lead-In (cut from the Noggin version)

Dick & Vern announce Carlablanca saying, "Watch the sketch and learn about rounding."

Matinee Movie: Cartablanca (EKA: #107) (cut from the Noggin version)

As 3 characters attemp to leave Cartablanca by plane, an Inspector rounds up their weights to make sure that they do not exceed the maximum load.

Mathnet: The Case of the Galling Stones - Part 1

George, Grecco, & Middlemun search Pat's apartment after Hestor Phestor accuses her of stealing a bracelet. They find it there: a gold dodecahedron with a letter on each face, hainging from a chain.

Captain Greco: It is Monday, 6:43 A.M. and school children throughout New York were playing the new schoolyard game

(sings)

Brooklyn Bridge is falling down

falling down, falling down...

as were the Manhattan, the GW, and the Tri-Boro. I was commanding the day watch out of Mathnet. If I sound a little neverous, it's because I'm Joe Greco. I'm not used to doing voiceovers. Pat Tuesday usually does them, but I had a task to perform. A difficult task.
